The paper deals with a geometric data structure problem, specifically the closest pair problem in the plane. This suggests that it would likely fall under the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of a data structure and its query time, indicating that it may also fall under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of range searching techniques further supports this. The paper also mentions the aspect ratio of query rectangles, which suggests that it may be relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or computer vision (cs.CV) applications. Finally, the reduction of the problem to standard range searching problems suggests that it may also be relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
